racist, all right?

13:21.067 --> 13:22.933
I'm a crusader
for the little guy.

13:22.935 --> 13:24.802
We don't need people like you.
I meant...

13:24.804 --> 13:27.671
I meant the underrepresented.
Uh-huh.

13:27.673 --> 13:29.673
[ Explosions continue ] Yeah, look,
I didn't even wanna come here

13:29.675 --> 13:32.042
'cause it's inappropriate.
How is <i>this</i> inappropriate?

13:32.044 --> 13:32.977
Are you kidding me?

13:32.979 --> 13:35.012
All of your aztec dancers
are white.

13:35.014 --> 13:37.982
So what? We're celebrating
the liberation

13:37.984 --> 13:39.116
of an oppressed people.

13:39.118 --> 13:41.352
You're celebrating
genocide, okay?

13:41.354 --> 13:43.187
[ People murmuring ]
Am I losing my mind here?

13:43.189 --> 13:46.023
No, no, you are not.
Thank you.

13:46.025 --> 13:49.126
We common sense folk need
to stick together. We do.

13:49.128 --> 13:51.195
We're all walking
on eggshells,

13:51.197 --> 13:52.262
and over what? Words?

13:52.264 --> 13:54.798
Exactly. Words.
They're just words!

13:54.800 --> 13:56.967
We have to examine
the intent behind them.

13:56.969 --> 13:58.836
It's like we can't say
anything anymore.

13:58.838 --> 14:01.338
I mean, first we couldn't
say "yellow." Mm.

14:01.340 --> 14:02.706
Then we couldn't say
"Oriental."

14:02.708 --> 14:05.142
Next, you're gonna tell me
we can't say "ching-chong."

14:05.144 --> 14:06.877
[ Scoffs ] Yeah. You can
-- you can never say that.

14:06.879 --> 14:08.412
Well, then, hell, what am i
supposed to call him?

14:08.414 --> 14:10.781
Yeah, you could just call me by my name.
Yeah, which is...

14:10.783 --> 14:13.851
Which is Brian.
No. How do I describe him?

14:13.853 --> 14:15.319
There's a guy right there
named Brian.

14:15.321 --> 14:17.955
Thank you. Oh, can we
even use "Brian" anymore?

14:17.957 --> 14:21.659
Or is that only something
that Brians call each other?

14:21.661 --> 14:22.893
What?
Nate. Nate, what the hell?

14:22.895 --> 14:24.828
Babe, thank god.
Back me up here.

14:24.830 --> 14:27.097
What -- what do you
call this right here?

14:27.099 --> 14:30.100
What? His chest? No, no, no.
The hole in the armor.

14:30.102 --> 14:32.036
A hole.
No. No. The expression, babe.

14:32.038 --> 14:37.675
I don't know! I-I -- a weakness
in the armor? No! It's a chink.

14:37.677 --> 14:38.375
Whoa!
Crowd: Ohh!

14:38.377 --> 14:40.744
Oh, my god! Nate.
Why would you say that?

14:40.746 --> 14:42.146
No. He's talking about
the chink in the armor,

14:42.148 --> 14:44.682
who apparently prefers
to be called "Brian."

14:44.684 --> 14:46.316
[ Crowd gasps ]
Lady, shut the [Bleep] up.

14:46.318 --> 14:47.685
Shut up!
Nate, Nate, Nate, Nate.

14:47.687 --> 14:49.286
Just, please,
say you're sorry and let's go.

14:49.288 --> 14:52.956
No, I'm not apologizing. Okay?
Because I'm right!

14:52.958 --> 14:54.391
You know what word
you shouldn't call people?

14:54.393 --> 14:58.128
Is "racist," okay? 'Cause it
makes you feel, like, this big.

14:58.130 --> 14:59.797
That's it.

14:59.799 --> 15:01.432
What's it?

15:01.434 --> 15:04.702
Oh, dude, dude. No, no. No!
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

15:04.704 --> 15:07.337
[ Crowd screams and gasps ]

15:07.339 --> 15:10.140
He can't swim!
[ Crowd clamoring ]

15:10.142 --> 15:11.308
I accept your challenge, Jesus.

15:11.310 --> 15:14.178
[ Crowd shouting indistinctly
and screaming ]

15:14.180 --> 15:17.948
Come to me, little man!
Come into my arms for Jesus.

15:17.950 --> 15:22.786
[ Crowd clamoring ] Minister:
Baptism is real! Come into my arms!

15:22.788 --> 15:26.423
[ Applause ]

15:26.425 --> 15:29.226
I saved
the little baby Jesus!

15:30.296 --> 15:31.829
You okay?

15:31.831 --> 15:32.496
Yes.

15:32.498 --> 15:33.864
Do we need to call a session
of family court?

15:33.866 --> 15:37.735
No. Family court is to decide
what TV show to watch,

15:37.737 --> 15:38.969
not to decide whether or not

15:38.971 --> 15:40.571
I'm some sort of
angry old white guy.

15:40.573 --> 15:43.574
Well, the court says you have
power over one of those things.

15:43.576 --> 15:46.810
I heard the whole thing,
and I think dad was right.

15:46.812 --> 15:49.113
Yeah, your dad likes
to think he's right.

15:49.115 --> 15:50.881
Since you weren't there
from the beginning

15:50.883 --> 15:53.083
and you don't have any
empirical scientific proof,

15:53.085 --> 15:55.052
maybe it's worth believing
in dad for once.

15:55.054 --> 15:56.954
Yeah, okay. Well, I see
what you're doing.

15:56.956 --> 15:58.956
Let's say -- just say
for argument's sake,

15:58.958 --> 16:00.057
I do believe
your father's right.

16:00.059 --> 16:02.659
Don't you think your rightness
comes at a heavy price?

16:02.661 --> 16:05.696
What price?
Your children's happiness?

16:05.698 --> 16:06.797
My happiness. Yours.

16:06.799 --> 16:10.634
Or maybe
just finishing dinner?

16:10.636 --> 16:13.771
The prosecution rests.

16:13.773 --> 16:17.274
♪♪

16:18.811 --> 16:21.845
[ Groans ]

16:21.847 --> 16:23.046
You okay, pal?

16:23.048 --> 16:24.882
No. I feel really bad.

16:24.884 --> 16:28.786
Why? What's wrong? I think it was
the thing at the restaurant.

16:28.788 --> 16:30.487
Oh.
[ Groans ]

16:30.489 --> 16:33.157
Yeah, I feel pretty bad
about that, too.

16:33.159 --> 16:34.725
What do I always
tell you guys?

16:34.727 --> 16:36.627
If a word hurts
somebody's feelings,

16:36.629 --> 16:37.561
you just don't say it.

16:37.563 --> 16:39.863
Yeah. My guts are all
twisted up.

16:39.865 --> 16:42.966
Yeah, you know what that is?
That's guilt.

16:42.968 --> 16:46.436
God, I should've just
apologized.

16:46.438 --> 16:47.805
I think I need to let it out.

16:47.807 --> 16:51.708
You know what, pal?
[ Moaning ]

16:51.710 --> 16:54.044
I think I do, too.

16:54.046 --> 16:55.679
[ Moans ]

16:55.681 --> 16:59.349
♪♪

17:41.026 --> 17:43.894
[ Yawns loudly ]

17:47.566 --> 17:48.932
Hey, buddy.

17:48.934 --> 17:50.934
Hey, man. Hey, guy.

17:50.936 --> 17:53.770
Uh, Brian. Hey. Oh, hey. What
are you doing here, man?

17:53.772 --> 17:55.539
I -- I'm -- listen, I got
something to say to you.

17:55.541 --> 17:57.474
You know, I actually have
something to say to you.

17:57.476 --> 17:59.509
Yeah, me, too. I-I...
Can I finish, please?

17:59.511 --> 18:01.745
You know, I feel like
I didn't effectively

18:01.747 --> 18:02.913
communicate my point.
Mm-hmm.

18:02.915 --> 18:05.182
I feel like I should've said
you were culturally insensitive

18:05.184 --> 18:07.184
instead of racist, even though,
that's what you were being. Well --

18:07.186 --> 18:08.752
yeah, because if you say
the word "racist,"

18:08.754 --> 18:10.687
it just shuts down
the conversation.

18:10.689 --> 18:11.889
You know,
you get so defensive,

18:11.891 --> 18:13.657
you can't even hear what
I'm trying to say. Mm-hmm.

18:13.659 --> 18:17.794
And all I'm trying to say is
the word hurts my feelings.

18:17.796 --> 18:19.096
Yeah.

18:19.098 --> 18:22.032
[ Weakly ] Montezuma.

18:22.034 --> 18:23.600
Why are we back here?

18:23.602 --> 18:25.903
Revenge.
What?

18:25.905 --> 18:27.204
[ Screaming, explosions ]

18:27.206 --> 18:28.772
[ Voice echoing ] Revenge.
[ Thud ]

18:28.774 --> 18:31.208
For three days, we've been
serving people shells

18:31.210 --> 18:33.510
full of decomposing flesh.

18:33.512 --> 18:35.612
[ Shouting and screaming ]

18:35.614 --> 18:37.681
For the record, a little more to
Montezuma's storyline

18:37.683 --> 18:39.483
than fecal urgency.

18:39.485 --> 18:40.117
[ Growls ]

18:40.119 --> 18:43.687
[ Stomach gurgling ] I mean, I work
at an i-95 rest stop, all right?

18:43.689 --> 18:44.888
D-do you have a bathroom
i can use?

18:44.890 --> 18:48.425
It's like, oh, I hear
that word like 50 times a day.

18:48.427 --> 18:49.660
I'm -- I'm sorry. Dude, dude,

18:49.662 --> 18:51.795
dude, I'm so sorry.
[ Unzips pants ]

18:51.797 --> 18:53.597
You see? That's all I
wanted to hear. Yeah.

18:53.599 --> 18:54.998
Thank you.
[ Flatulence ]

18:55.000 --> 18:56.633
Hey, what the...

18:56.635 --> 18:57.601
Hello?
Oh, shit.

18:57.603 --> 18:59.703
[ Flatulence, liquid splatters ]
What are you doing?

18:59.705 --> 19:00.637
Oh, my god!
Ew!

19:00.639 --> 19:02.906
I'm sorry. There's a
bathroom like 20 feet away!

19:02.908 --> 19:04.107
I didn't have time
to get there!

19:04.109 --> 19:06.543
[ Liquid splatters ] Did you come
back here to shit on my restaurant?

19:06.545 --> 19:08.545
I didn't.
[ Flatulence, liquid splatters ]

19:08.547 --> 19:11.214
Oh, my god.
Don't look at me!

19:11.216 --> 19:13.817
I'll do the rest
behind those bushes.

19:13.819 --> 19:16.053
Nate! Help me!
I can't get it open!

19:16.055 --> 19:16.920
Fonzie it!
What?!

19:16.922 --> 19:19.856
Fonzie! Oh, shit! Ohh!
[ Flatulence, liquid splatters ]

19:19.858 --> 19:21.591
Oh, really?!
Oh, yeah.

19:21.593 --> 19:23.160
You're shitting on my car,
too?!

19:23.162 --> 19:24.161
I forgot it was your car!

19:24.163 --> 19:25.963
It's the only car in the lot!
[ Liquid continues flowing ]

19:25.965 --> 19:27.898
I'm sorry!
Sorry? Too late for sorry!

19:27.900 --> 19:29.032
[ Groans ]
[ Liquid splatters]

19:29.034 --> 19:32.769
How do I make this right? There's
no way to make this right!

19:32.771 --> 19:33.971
[ Flatulence, liquid splatters ]
Man!

19:33.973 --> 19:38.842
I-I can buy some merchandise!
Do you have any toilet paper?!

19:38.844 --> 19:42.779
Robin: What is happening?!

19:42.781 --> 19:45.849
[ Water whooshing,
liquid splatting ]

19:45.851 --> 19:48.552
[ Coughing ]

19:48.554 --> 19:52.255
Oh, oh!
Why did you use your sleeves?

19:52.257 --> 19:54.224
Why didn't you just use
your socks?

19:54.226 --> 19:56.193
I did. Okay?

19:56.195 --> 19:58.061
I used everything I had.

19:58.063 --> 20:00.030
You wanna switch places?
No.

20:00.032 --> 20:01.264
No, I didn't think so.

20:01.266 --> 20:07.337
Conquistador cast:
♪ teno-shit-lan ♪

20:07.339 --> 20:09.706
Hey!
Man: What do you want?!

20:11.443 --> 20:12.943
♪♪

20:12.945 --> 20:13.610
Billy Evans?

20:13.612 --> 20:16.246
Which one of you
overprivileged white kids

20:16.248 --> 20:18.949
is Billy Evans?
Yeah, over here.

20:18.951 --> 20:21.551
Okay.
We're from P.F.R. Industries.

20:21.553 --> 20:23.220
Yep.
You're in possession

20:23.222 --> 20:25.322
of stolen property
that we're here to collect.

20:25.324 --> 20:27.057
Oh, I'm sorry, girl.
There's this little thing

20:27.059 --> 20:29.993
called reporter's privilege.
Yeah, look it up. I did.

20:29.995 --> 20:32.829
